  "prompt": "Last year my score for CAT was around 40 percentile. What should I do to score > 90  percentile this year?",
  "response": "Improving your CAT percentile from 40 to above 90 requires a strategic approach and consistent effort. Here are some steps to help you achieve this goal:\n\n1. **Understand the Exam Structure**: Familiarize yourself with the CAT exam pattern, sections, and marking scheme. The sections include Quantitative Ability (QA), Verbal Ability and Reading Comprehension (VARC), and Data Interpretation and Logical Reasoning (DILR).\n\n2. **Analyze Previous Performance**: Identify the areas where you struggled last year. Understanding your weaknesses will help you focus your preparation effectively.\n\n3. **Build Strong Fundamentals**: Ensure you have a solid grasp of basic concepts in all sections. Use standard textbooks and online resources to strengthen your foundation.\n\n4. **Create a Study Plan**: Develop a detailed study plan that covers all topics and allows for regular revision. Allocate more time to weaker areas while maintaining a balance across all sections.\n\n5. **Practice Regularly**: Solve sample papers, previous years' papers, and take mock tests regularly. This will help you get accustomed to the exam format and improve your time management skills.\n\n6. **Analyze Mock Tests**: After each mock test, analyze your performance thoroughly. Identify the types of questions you got wrong and understand the reasons behind them. This will help you avoid similar mistakes in the future.\n\n7. **Improve Speed and Accuracy**: Work on increasing your speed without compromising accuracy. Practice various shortcuts and problem-solving techniques that can save time during the exam.\n\n8. **Enhance Reading Skills**: For the VARC section, develop a habit of reading newspapers, magazines, and books regularly. This will improve your reading comprehension and vocabulary.\n\n9. **Work on Logical Reasoning**: For the DILR section, practice puzzles, games, and logical reasoning problems. This will help you think critically and solve complex problems efficiently.\n\n10. **Stay Updated**: Keep yourself updated with current affairs and general knowledge, as this can sometimes be beneficial in understanding the context of certain questions.\n\n11. **Seek Guidance**: Consider joining a coaching institute or online classes if you need additional support. Experienced mentors can provide valuable insights and personalized guidance.\n\n12. **Maintain a Positive Attitude**: Stay motivated and confident throughout your preparation. A positive mindset can significantly impact your performance.\n\n13. **Healthy Lifestyle**: Ensure you maintain a balanced diet, get adequate sleep, and engage in physical activities to keep your mind and body fit.\n\nRemember, consistency and perseverance are key to achieving a high percentile in CAT. Keep track of your progress and adjust your strategies as needed. Good luck!",
